post_text:
The Bruins are at Frankton tonight to start the CIC season. Kick-off is set for 7pm. The Blackford Sports network will not be broadcasting tonight, but WPGW will be there so listen in!

There will likely be minimal, at best, coverage online including on Max Preps. But we'll do the best we can to put something out there if possible.

Good luck Bruins!

And a reminder from the heart....

PLEASE TAKE A MASK. TRUST ME, IT IS RECOMMENDED. AND WHATEVER YOU DO, MINIMALLY FOR THE SAFETY OF ALL OUR FANS AND KIDS, SOCIAL DISTANCE. DON'T TAKE A CHANCE.

Thank you and enjoy the game!

post_text:
Congrats to Quinten Teer!

(copy of Twitter release by Star Press)

The votes are in and the first winner of The Star Press Football Player of the Week award goes to Blackford's Quinten Teer.

The senior running back led the nominees after racking up 94 total yards in Blackford's 28-23 loss against Wes-Del. Teer ran the ball 10 times for 72 yards, scored twice on the ground (including a touchdown on the Bruins' last drive), caught a pass for 22 yards and defended three passes.|

Teer is coming off a 2019 season where he finished second among Blackford runners with 644 yards and five touchdowns. This offseason, he transition from fullback to the team's lead running back. His 22 receiving yards in Week 1 surpassed his total (20 yards) from last season.

Teer led the high turnout of voters this week, which more than doubled the highest turnout from last season (2,125 votes). Teer took home 34.83% (1,533 votes) of the 4,402 votes cast. Behind him was Monroe Central's Luke Jones (30.17%, 1,328 votes), Wes-Del's Will Kelly (24.01%, 1,057 votes) and Yorktown's JJ Evans (11%, 484 votes).

We are looking for someone, maybe two, who might be interested in helping organize youth travel fall baseball. I have some info about kids who might be interested and the prior person who helped us out is interested in helping fill you in on what has been done.

This is not a school role or a paid position, but it would be great to have someone interested who would be willing to work with developing younger kids on "The Bruin Way" to help prepare upcoming Future Bruins.

A recent Bruin baseball player could fit this role well as a coach or someone who could help find coaches for teams.

Contact me at tuggen@blackfordschools.org if interested.

post_text:
JH Football had very low numbers as of this morning. Low as in....if we don't get more players, we may not have a team!

Good news is that a few more joined today, but we need a lot more players to make sure and, ideally, to have two teams.

Football is a fun sport to play and numbers help tremendously.

Consider playing! Practice starts tomorrow after school. Remember to complete your Final Forms online registration and turn a physical (or health questionnaire in if using last year's physical).

We have come so far in football the past 3 years. We need you to keep things rolling!!

See Coach Dawson or Coach Leavitt if interested!

post_text:
UPDATE: We are still looking! Please help us out so we have a chain crew for FB games. :)

We are looking for a few people to help us out with chains on Friday nights and JH football games on Tuesday nights. There are only 3 regular season games for both teams. And the varsity does have a scrimmage this Saturday that we need a couple people to work.

Good news is you will see the games live as we will probably have very limited numbers of fans due to Covid.

If you are interested, please contact Tony Uggen, A.D. at tuggen@blackfordschools.org as soon as possible.

We will be using just 3 on Saturday and JH games. We use 4 for varsity football regular season games. If we have more volunteers, we will rotate everyone. Pay is $20 per night.

post_text:
A reminder to seniors who have yet to be featured to send me your responses and a picture for your Senior Spotlight. Right now we have enough in to run them through tomorrow. We could use several more soon.

Here are the questions to answer for your Spotlight:
Sports or activities you were involved in while in high school?
Favorite BHS moment(s)?
Any advice for underclassmen?
Anyone you would like to thank for helping/supporting you along the way?
Future plans?

A horizontal picture works best, but I can adjust the pic if necessary to make it work.

Send your info to me at tuggen@blackfordschools.org.

Thanks!

Freshman Riata Rouch is spending her time practicing horses, as she is qualified for the YEDA (Youth Equestrian Development Association) Nationals for the 2019-2020 school year. The National competition has been rescheduled for June in Springfield, Illinois.

Riata finished Reserve National Champion last year, after leading the Nation in both of her classes.

She represents Blackford County Schools on two different equestrian teams. She is also a member of the BJSHS tennis team.

Good luck at Nationals!

Thank you all for a great 4-year run!

post_text:
Passing along to Bruin Swimmers (this was also sent to you via Final Forms)...

With the new “normal” I wanted to reach out and tell my seniors I am truly sorry for how this year has ended for you. Truly heartbreaking. We will be hand out varsity letters, awards and patches at some point. We just don’t know when or what this might look like. Please continue to exercise and eat healthy. We may have a summer swim program BUT if we do it will not start until mid to late July. This will depend on many factors and we will keep you informed as soon as we know anything. You are all in my prayers and hope to see you soon.

Thank you,
Kristie Malott
Blackford County Schools Athletics
